e disruption, creating a ternary/multiple system. We find that secondary\nfission typically occurs within the first five hours after the contact binary\nseparates, and is more common when the secondary is less dense or more\nelongated.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 23 Jun 2022 09:30:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-09-14"}
